The issue is that multiple goroutines are checking the token expiry and refreshing concurrently. You can fix this with a `sync.Mutex` or `singleflight.Group`.

Here's the recommended approach using `singleflight`:

```go
var refreshGroup singleflight.Group

func RefreshToken(ctx context.Context) (*Token, error) {
    v, err, _ := refreshGroup.Do("refresh", func() (interface{}, error) {
        return doRefresh(ctx)
    })
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
    return v.(*Token), nil
}
```

This ensures only one refresh executes at a time, and all concurrent callers share the result.

Good catch. Add a retry wrapper that detects 401 responses and triggers a fresh refresh:

```go
func CallWithRetry(ctx context.Context, fn func(token string) error) error {
    token, err := GetCachedToken(ctx)
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }
    err = fn(token)
    if isUnauthorized(err) {
        token, err = RefreshToken(ctx)
        if err != nil {
            return err
        }
        return fn(token)
    }
    return err
}
```

This gives you exactly-once refresh semantics with automatic retry.
